gomodel:SYNGO_2395  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Results section: \"Endogenous Formation of ATP in the PSD\"\n\n- Literal: \"...the PSD fractions\nwere incubated with ADP, D,L-G3P, NAD, and 32Pi. The\namount of ATP formed endogenously was determined by the\nCa21yCaM-dependent phosphorylation of the PSD proteins\n(Fig. 6, lanes 1 and 2).\"\n\n\"By using the kinase activity to estimate the ATP\namount, our results indicated that, in three independent\nexperiments, the ATP formed endogenously was 369, 360, and\n353 fmol ATP per mg PSD, resulting in an average yield of\n361 6 2.1 fmol ATP per mg PSD protein. Endogenous\nformation of ATP with rat cortex PSD was similar to that using\nthe porcine PSD (data not shown).\". Experimental description: Species used was: porcine - Sus scrofa.\n\nMethods:\n\n-Literal: \"Adult porcine brain, obtained from a local slaughter house, was dissected, and the cerebral cortex was employed for the studies illustrated in the figures\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6893-6177" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5265-6306" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-01" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2395" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9823" .

